Package com.binance4j.core.symbolfilter

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    IcebergPartsFilter
    Defines the maximum parts an iceberg order can have.
    LotSizeFilter
    Defines the quantity (aka "lots" in auction terms) rules for a symbol.
    MarketLotSizeFilter
    Defines the quantity (aka "lots" in auction terms) rules for MARKET orders on a symbol.
    MaxNumAlgoOrdersFilter
    Defines the maximum number of orders an account is allowed to have open on a symbol.
    MaxNumIcebergOrdersFilter
    Defines the allowed maximum position an account can have on the base asset of a symbol.
    MaxNumOrdersFilter
    Defines the maximum number of orders an account is allowed to have open on a symbol.
    MaxPositionFilter
    Defines the allowed maximum position an account can have on the base asset of a symbol.
    MinNotionalFilter
    Defines the minimum notional value allowed for an order on a symbol.
    NotionalFilter
    Defines the acceptable notional range allowed for an order on a symbol.
    PercentPriceBySideFilter
    Defines the valid range for the price based on the lastPrice of the symbol.
    PercentPriceFilter
    Defines valid range for a price based on the average of the previous trades.
    PriceFilter
    Defines the price rules for a symbol.
    SymbolFilters
    The trading rules of a symbol
    SymbolFiltersDeserializer
    SymbolFilters deserializer
    TrailingDeltaFilter
    Defines the minimum and maximum value for the parameter trailingDelta.
